Method Detail

load

public void load(com.google.gwt.core.ext.typeinfo.JClassType module,
                 java.util.Map<java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation>,java.util.List<com.google.gwt.core.ext.typeinfo.JClassType>> scanResult)
          throws InvalidMvp4gConfigurationException
Loads all Mvp4g elements from an in-memory representation of the XML configuration and/or annotations.

Configuration loading comprises up to three phases:
  1. Phase 1, Parsing all the XML elements (if there is an XML configuration file): during this phase, all the Mvp4gElement instances are constructed from their corresponding xml tags. Simple validation of element attributes is performed.
  2. Phase 2, Parsing all the annotations: during this phase, all the Mvp4gElement instances are constructed from their corresponding annotations. All possible validations are performed.
  3. Phase 3, Validation of cross-element references and removal of useless elements: in this phase element identifiers are checked for global uniqueness; event handler references and view references are checked for existence. Validity elements class is also checked.

Parameters:
module - module to load
scanResult - Map of classes associated with an annotation
Throws:
InvalidMvp4gConfigurationException - this exception is thrown where a configuration error occurs.
